 113:indcpa.c      **** /*************************************************
 114:indcpa.c      **** * Name:        indcpa_enc_cmp
 115:indcpa.c      **** *
 116:indcpa.c      **** * Description: Re-encryption function.
 117:indcpa.c      **** *              Compares the re-encypted ciphertext with the original ciphertext byte per byte.
 118:indcpa.c      **** *              The comparison is performed in a constant time manner.
 119:indcpa.c      **** *
 120:indcpa.c      **** *
 121:indcpa.c      **** * Arguments:   - unsigned char *ct:         pointer to input ciphertext to compare the new cipherte
 122:indcpa.c      **** *              - const unsigned char *m:    pointer to input message (of length KYBER_INDCPA_MSGBYT
 123:indcpa.c      **** *              - const unsigned char *pk:   pointer to input public key (of length KYBER_INDCPA_PUB
 124:indcpa.c      **** *              - const unsigned char *coin: pointer to input random coins used as seed (of length K
 125:indcpa.c      **** *                                           to deterministically generate all randomness
 126:indcpa.c      **** * Returns:     - boolean byte indicating that re-encrypted ciphertext is NOT equal to the original 
 127:indcpa.c      **** **************************************************/
